Fedora Security Lab - Simple presentation
=========================================
This simple presentation about the Fedora Security Lab is using the shower
javascript library (http://github.com/pepelsbey/shower). It's designed for 
short presentations or ligthning talks. This is the reason why only basic
content is included, the rest needs to be in your brain or on your notes. 

Download
--------
The source is located in the git repository of the Security Spin.

$ git clone git://git.fedorahosted.org/git/security-spin.git/

Now change to the 'presentations/2012-simple' directory.

Usage
-----
Open the file index.html in the lastest version of a browser (eg. Firefox > 10,
Google Chrome).

* Click any slide to enter presentation mode
* Use arrow keys to navigate
* Press 'Esc' to exit presentation mode

Or use just a keyboard to navigate:

* Press right arrow key to select first slide
* Press 'Enter' to enter presentation mode
* Press 'Esc' to exit presentation mode

